	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001132_0001"/><!--pb/@n='83r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadleigh House</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Highbury New Park</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">12<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I beg to 
<lb/>acknowledge the 
<lb/>receipt of two 
<lb/>notes of hand of 
<lb/>eight &amp; ten months 
<lb/>date <add place="above">each</add> for Â£1050 this 
<lb/>morning &amp; return you 
<lb/>my best thanks 
<lb/>for the same.

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001132_0002"/><!--pb/@n='83v'--> 
<lb/>We came out here 
<lb/>last night and 
<lb/>remain a few 
<lb/>days in quiet, 
<lb/>though I fear that 
<lb/>I must come to 
<lb/>the West End for 
<lb/>a dinner this 
<lb/>evening - at 
<lb/><persName>Captain Washington's</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I have got a bad 
<lb/>cold &amp; only hope 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001132_0003"/><!--pb/@n='84r'--> 
<lb/>it will be better 
<lb/>before going to 
<lb/><placeName>Oxford</placeName>. I am 
<lb/>thus out of 
<lb/><persName>Arrowsmith<reg>'</reg>s</persName> beat 
<lb/>so you must 
<lb/>apply some other 
<lb/>long pole to stir 
<lb/>him up. Set <persName>Cooke</persName>
<lb/>at him! My 
<lb/>brother will call 
<lb/>for my letters. </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001132_0004"/><!--pb/@n='84v'-->
<lb/><p>My friends all 
<lb/>call out against 
<lb/>the portrait by 
<lb/><persName>Philips</persName>, <persName>Vardon</persName>
<lb/>says it will do 
<lb/>for any one between 
<lb/><persName>Captain Cook</persName> &amp; 
<lb/><persName>Guy Fawkes</persName>! </p>
			
</div>
